status_message: TONIGHT on POV at 10/9c.  The Zabuli School first opened in 2008, and it did so while the surrounding population eyed it with suspicion, fear and even open hostility. Although remarkable changes happen when a community skeptical about girls' education learns to embrace it, the threats that girls face ‚Äì from forced marriage to Taliban attack ‚Äì loom large. See how against all odds, these students work towards an education in 'What Tomorrow Brings.'
link_name: Threats - What Tomorrow Brings - POV | PBS

status_message: TONIGHT on POV at 10/9c.  While the girls learn to read and write in 'What Tomorrow Brings,' their education goes far beyond the classroom to become lessons about tradition and time. They discover their school is the one place they can turn to understand the differences between the lives they were born into and the lives they dream of leading. Watch how despite their chaotic, violent present, these girls aim to complete their education.
link_name: Letter - What Tomorrow Brings - POV | PBS

status_message: TONIGHT on POV at 10/9c. With unprecedented access, 'What Tomorrow Brings' goes inside the very first girls' school in one small Afghan village. Never before have fathers here allowed their daughters to be educated, and they aren't sure they even want to now.  From the school's beginnings to its first graduation, the film traces the interconnected stories of students, teachers, village elders, parents, and school founder Razia Jan. See the ripple effect that happens when girls' are educated.
link_name: What Tomorrow Brings - Trailer - Oct. 31 on PBS

link_name: Women's Rights - Hooligan Sparrow - tonight on POV

status_message: Live from the red carpet premiere of Hamilton's America. Catch the premiere on Great Performances l PBS Friday at 9/8c.

Because of her activism and advocacy work, Ye Haiyan (aka Hooligan Sparrow) faces government surveillance, harassment and imprisonment. When filmmaker Nanfu Wang began documenting Hooligan Sparrow, she then faced destroyed cameras and intimidation. Yet she managed to smuggle the footage out of China to tell the story of a seemingly impossible battle for human rights. Known as the film China doesn't want you to see, don't miss the U.S. broadcast premiere of Hooligan Sparrow tonight on POV.
link_name: Censorship - Hooligan Sparrow - tonight on POV

status_message: Government surveillance, secret police, threats and arrests ‚Äî the danger is palpable as filmmaker Nanfu Wang follows maverick activist Ye Haiyan (aka Hooligan Sparrow) and her band of colleagues to southern China.
